claim.claim-text:
An apparatus in a radio access network, comprising:
means (902, 906, 908) for receiving (300) a service request comprising service requirements of a service;
means (902, 906) for determining (302), based on the service request, a service level specification of the service, the service level specification comprising performance parameters and network functions to support the requested service;
means (902, 906) for normalising (304) the determined service level specification by scaling the performance parameters according into a given normalisation model of the network to obtain normalised service level specification;
means (902, 906) for determining (306), based on the network functions and the given normalisation model, normalised performance capability of the network functions and a configuration of a network slice supporting the requested service;
means (902, 906) for comparing (308) the normalised service level specification to the normalised performance capability;
means (902, 906) for determining (310), based on the comparison, whether the requested service can be realised with the network slice, and if so, create the slice, and if not, determine from the service level agreement data if requirements in the service request comprise acceptable reductions, with which the requested service could be realised.

The apparatus of claim 1, further comprising:
means for determining one or more alternative configurations and normalised performance capabilities of a network slice supporting the requested service;
means for comparing the normalised service level specifications of the one or more alternative configurations to the normalised performance capability.

A method, comprising:
receiving (300) a service request comprising service requirements;
determining (302), based on the service request, service level specification of the request, the service level specification comprising performance parameters and network functions to support the requested service;
normalising (304) the determined service level specification by scaling the performance parameters according into a given normalisation model of the network to obtain normalised service level specification;
determining (306), based on the network functions and the given normalisation model, normalised performance capability of the network functions and a configuration of a network slice supporting the requested service;
comparing (308) the normalised service level specification to the normalised performance capability; and
determining (310), based on the comparison, whether the requested service can be realised with the network slice, and if so, create the slice, and if not, determining from the service level agreement data if requirements in the service request comprise acceptable reductions, with which the requested service could be realised.

The method of claim 8, further comprising:
determining one or more alternative configurations and normalised performance capabilities of a network slice supporting the requested service;
comparing the normalised service level specifications of the one or more alternative configurations to the normalised performance capability.

A computer program comprising instructions for causing an apparatus to perform at least the following:
receiving (300) a service request comprising service requirements of a service;
determining (302), based on the service request, a service level specification of the requested service, the service level specification comprising performance parameters and network functions to support the requested service;
normalising (304) the determined service level specification by scaling the performance parameters according into a given normalisation model of the network to obtain normalised service level specification;
determining (306), based on the network functions and the given normalisation model, normalised performance capability of the network functions and a configuration of a network slice supporting the requested service;
comparing (308) the normalised service level specification to the normalised performance capability; and
determining (310), based on the comparison, whether the requested service can be realised with the network slice, and if so, create the slice, and if not, determine from the service level agreement data if requirements in the service request comprise acceptable reductions, with which the requested service could be realised.
